text: The plot seems weird, why would Vince want to direct a movie? he is the laziest guy ever, he just likes to be an actor, party and chill with the boys. Also he would never direct something that he hasn't written himself he is really ego about that sort of stuff. Secondly if Ari is the new studio head, i believe he took over from John Ellis that means that he now runs everything, why would a 100 milj dollar movie being canceled ruin his career. When smokejumpers was canceled that didn't ruin John Ellis career, Dana Gordon even said, he is the head of the studio, he can do whatever he wants and I quote - "This is why I hire women to blow me, not run my studio" meaning that I might have to blow him to keep my job. So the plot for this movie makes no sense really, I like though the parts with Johnny drama and Turtle in the trailer. I just don't get the main plot. It should be the head of the studio buying something big like a new franchise like "Starwars" for 4billion dollars or maybe buying another studio in asia somewhere, something really big like trying to film an action sequence in space like James Cameron would try to do if he could, and Vince and the gang have already conquered everything in the world, he is even married,  he should be more about taking it easy and pursuing other things above money and fame etc, a perfect thing would be Ari wanting Vinny to take over a new franchise but he just wants to do a documentary somewhere and it becomes the most expensive and impossible documentary ever, in space! haha, it needs to be something more creative and surprising!

text: I came here to comment, not watch the trailer again. Former huge fan of the show, I binge-watched every season repeatedly as a sort of reality escape not to be taken too seriously, so just self-indulgent escapism. But at some point around season 6 I was looking for some kind of redemption for these self-absorbed shallow characters, but it never really happened, with seasons 7 and 8 sucking horribly. But the ultimate crucifixion of my love for Entourage was The Movie. Watched it once then had to sort of go puke and take a long shower to wash away the filth. Having seen that movie and watch these assholes just fuck up everything and reveal how truly shallow and self-obsessed they are/were, it is no longer of interest to re-watch the show even when it was good (seasons 1-5). Yeah I know it's just a TV show and the characters read/act according to a script/director, but I'm now SO DONE with their brand of sensationalist amusement park ride lifestyle. Ultimately, Entourage just served as a bad tasting tribute to the shallow vacant selfish artificial fake greedy side of Hollywood and those who suck up to whoever is the current "celeb". Bleah! Have to vomit again. So goodbye Entourage and the shitty fake materialistic selfish world it represents. Hurl!
